          A Remote WebView architecture renders a remote server UI directly in the local app without a frontend build,
          and it implements mistral.rs-based local LLM inference, NAT traversal via a Bore tunnel, and automatic switching between 3 operating modes (local/remote/hybrid).
        </p>
        <ul class="pf-project-highlights">
          <li>Rust Sidecar pattern &mdash; Python services auto start/stop with the app</li>
          <li>Remote WebView removes the frontend build &mdash; shorter deploy time</li>
          <li>Custom-built mistral.rs local LLM inference + Bore tunnel NAT traversal</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="pf-project-stack-row">
